sectiondef.header: Properties extracted from the 32-bit muon RoI word

briefdescription.para: Get the logic number of the highest threshold this RoI passed.
Get the "RoI number" (position inside the sector).

detaileddescription.para: A muon's spacial location is identified from the sector number and the hemisphere that detected it. Each sector is additionally divided into multiple areas, called RoIs that tell you which part of the sector the muon candidate was detected in.

briefdescription.para: Get the full sector address.

detaileddescription.para: The sector address is an 8-bit identifier of the sector. For its detailed description, see page 38 of https://edms.cern.ch/file/248757/1/mirod.pdf

The least significant bit shown which hemisphere the sector is in (0: positive side, 1: negative side), the upper (1 or 2) bits show what kind of sector it is, the rest of the address is the number of the sector.

briefdescription.para: Returns if the candidate had the highest pT in the sector.

detaileddescription.para: Each muon trigger sector can only send information about a maximum of two LVL1 muon candidate to the central trigger. If this flag is true, this candidate had the highest pT threshold assigned to it in its sector. If it's false, it was the second candidate in its sector.

briefdescription.para: Returns if there were other muons detected in the same RoI.

detaileddescription.para: One RoI (one part of the trigger sector) can only send information about one LVL1 muon candidate to the central trigger. This flag is true if the particular RoI that detected this muon candidate also detected another candidate with lower pT.

briefdescription.para: Returns if there were other muons detected in the same sector.

detaileddescription.para: This flag is set to true if the sector that this muon candidate came from, detected more than 2 LVL1 muon candidates.

briefdescription.para: Returns the system that detected the muon candidate.

detaileddescription.para: The function decodes the sector type encoded in the 8-bit sector address into an easy to understand enumeration.

briefdescription.para: Returns the hemisphere that detected the muon candidate.

detaileddescription.para: The function decodes the sector hemisphere encoded in the 8-bit sector address into an easy to understand enumeration.

briefdescription.para: Returns the charge sign of the muon candidate.

detaileddescription.para: Endcap and forward sectors can tell you what was the charge of the muon candidate. Barrel candidates can't do this.

briefdescription.para: Returns the veto flag for the candidate.

detaileddescription.para: When the overlap handling is activated in the MuCTPI, candidates can be ignored in the multiplicity sum sent to the CTP. This flag tells you whether this particular candidate was ignored in the multiplicity sum.

briefdescription.para: The muon candidate was detected in the barrel region.
The muon candidate was detected in the endcap region.
The muon candidate was detected in the forward region.
RoI source enumeration.
The candidate came from the +z side (side A).
The candidate came from the -z side (side C).
RoI hemisphere enumeration.

This class describes all the properties of a muon region of interest (RoI) in the xAOD format.
